of%20the%20%26quot%3BAfrica%26quot%3B%20in%20Lake%20Huron.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Yvonne%20Drebert%20and%20Zach%20Melnick%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFilmmakers%20shooting%20footage%20of%20invasive%20mussels%20in%20Lake%20Huron%20found%20a%20shipwreck%20from%201895.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%C2%A0%26quot%3BAfrica%26quot%3B%20had%20been%20carrying%20coal%20from%20Ohio%20to%20Ontario%2C%20and%20was%20carrying%2011%20sailors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20wreck%20is%20covered%20in%20invasive%20quagga%20mussels%20that%20are%20altering%20the%20Great%20Lakes'%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20pair%20of%20filmmakers%20who%20spent%20two%20years%20shooting%20footage%20for%20a%20documentary%20about%20invasive%20mussels%20in%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20accidentally%20discovered%20a%20128-year-old%20shipwreck%20that%20vanished%20in%201895.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wreck%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20the%20%26quot%3BAfrica%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20carrying%20coal%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%2011%20doomed%20sailors%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Ohio%20to%20Ontario%20in%20October%20of%201895%2C%20before%20disappearing%20into%20Lake%20Huron%20amid%20an%20early%20season%20snowstorm%2C%20according%20to%20the%20filmmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20century%20later%2C%20Yvonne%20Drebert%20and%20Zach%20Melnick%20received%20a%20tip%20from%20scientists%20while%20they%20were%20working%20on%20their%20documentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScientists%20doing%20an%20offshore%20fish%20survey%20had%20noticed%20an%20anomaly%20on%20their%20sonar%20readout%2C%20basically%20an%20unusual%20bump%20on%20an%20otherwise%20flat%20lakebed%2C%26quot%3B%20Melnick%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finspiredplanet.ca%2Funcategorized%2Fafrica-shipwreck-discovery%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20couple%2C%20who%20specialize%20in%20underwater%20videography%2C%20grabbed%20their%20ultra-low-light%2C%20high-resolution%20camera%20system%2C%20and%20journeyed%20out%20to%20the%20site%20of%20the%20anomaly%2C%20expecting%20to%20find%20%26quot%3Ba%20pile%20of%20rocks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20when%20their%20remotely%20operated%20vehicle%20descended%2085%20meters%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20huge%20structure%20loomed%20up%20from%20the%20depths%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20was%20a%20shipwreck.%20We%20couldn't%20believe%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Melnick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wreck%20was%20difficult%20to%20identify%20%E2%80%94%20images%20from%20the%20filmmakers%20show%20the%20ship%20is%20covered%20by%20the%20invasive%20quagga%20mussels%20that%20have%20been%20overhauling%20the%20ecosystem%20of%20the%20Great%20Lakes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22quagga%20mussels%20on%20shipwreck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656bb9300ec98e92f74b7d87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222408%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEvery%20inch%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BAfrica%26quot%3B%20is%20covered%20with%20invasive%20quagga%20mussels%2C%20which%20have%20been%20plaguing%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20for%20years.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Yvonne%20Drebert%20and%20Zach%20Melnick%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20filmmakers%20said%20that%20with%20the%20help%20of%20a%20local%20maritime%20historian%20and%20a%20marine%20archaeologist%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BAfrica%26quot%3B%20emerged%20as%20the%20likeliest%20possibility.%20The%20vessel's%20measurements%20matched%20that%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BAfrica%2C%26quot%3B%20plus%20Melnick%20and%20Drebert%20saw%20coal%20scattered%20across%20the%20lake%20bottom%20near%20the%20wreck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20quaggas%20filtering%20the%20Great%20Lakes%2C%20that%20the%20lakes%20are%C2%A0up%20to%20three%20times%20as%20clear%20as%20they%20were%20before%20the%20mussels%2C%26quot%3B%20Drebert%20said%20in%20the%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThe%20quaggas%20are%20the%20reason%20we're%20able%20to%20see%20the%20shipwreckin%20almost%20300%20feet%20of%20water%20without%20any%20additional%20lights.%20But%20they're%20also%20responsible%20for%20making%20wreck%20identification%20in%20the%20Great%20Lakes%20incredibly%20difficult.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple's%20documentary%2C%20%26quot%3BAll%20Too%20Clear%3A%20Beneath%20the%20Surface%20of%20the%20Great%20Lakes%2C%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20released%20in%20early%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffilmmakers-accidentally-discover-128-year-old-shipwreck-in-lake-huron-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701558655000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656bb96858e7c0c29a2907b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffilmmakers-accidentally-discover-128-year-old-shipwreck-in-lake-huron-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20filmmakers%20shooting%20a%20documentary%20about%20invasive%20mussels%20discovered%20a%20128-year-old%20shipwreck%20that%20sunk%20in%20an%201895%20snowstorm%20in%20Lake%20Huron.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmark%40businessinsider.com%20(Michelle%20Mark)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A335%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffilmmakers-accidentally-discover-128-year-old-shipwreck-in-lake-huron-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SZA%20on%20Redefining%20Hitmaker%20Status%20and%20Finding%20a%20Place%20For%20Her%20Sound%20After%20%E2%80%98Punching%20Up%E2%80%99%20For%20So%20Long%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701558066000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FScreenshot-2023-12-02-at-2.21.50-PM.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235818434%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SZA%20has%20been%20honored%20with%20Variety%E2%80%99s%20H