20unrelenting%20schedules%20have%20turned%20to%20alcohol%20and%20drugs%20to%20avoid%20seeking%20professional%20help%2C%20report%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222553%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Traffic%20Control%20Tower%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dd5bae3e94e8670ef6a6967%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221702%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERafael%20Cordero%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAir%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20who%20have%20long%20endured%20staffing%20shortages%2C%20are%20facing%20increasingly%20strenuous%20schedules.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20workloads%20have%20led%20some%20controllers%20to%20use%20alcohol%2C%20sleeping%20pills%2C%20and%20drugs%20to%20cope%2C%20per%20a%20Times%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EComplaints%20to%20the%20FAA%20revealed%20problems%20among%20the%20workforce%20that%20could%20jeopardize%20air%20safety.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20growing%20problem%20that's%20threatening%20the%20ability%20of%20air%20traffic%20controllers%20to%20effectively%20perform%20their%20jobs%2C%20which%20over%20time%20could%20weaken%20the%20safety%20of%20passengers%20in%20the%20skies%3A%20their%20strained%20workloads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20air%20traffic%20controller%20workforce%20in%20recent%20years%20has%20been%20stretched%20to%20the%20brink%2C%20with%20staffing%20shortages%20necessitating%20six-day%20workweeks%20and%2010-hour%20workdays%20for%20many%20controllers%2C%20conditions%20which%20have%20exacerbated%20exhaustion%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20led%20to%20depression%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F02%2Fbusiness%2Fair-traffic-controllers-safety.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20interviews%20and%20complaints%20sent%20to%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%2C%20several%20controllers%20said%20they%20had%20not%20sought%20personal%20help%20to%20deal%20with%20physical%20and%20psychological%20issues%20because%20they%20were%20fearful%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fpilot-mental-illness-faa-regulations-joseph-emerson-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAA's%20rules%20governing%20medical%20clearances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rules%20regulating%20the%20clearances%20prohibit%20particular%20medications%20from%20being%20used%20by%20air%20traffic%20controllers%20%E2%80%94%20as%20they%20could%20cause%20drowsiness%20on%20the%20job%20%E2%80%94%20so%20some%20controllers%20have%20turned%20to%20alcohol%20and%20sleeping%20pills%20instead%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20Some%20controllers%20have%20forgone%20medications%20that%20they%20needed%20in%20order%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20clearances.%20And%20a%20few%20controllers%20have%20even%20turned%20to%20drugs%2C%20based%20on%20a%20Times%20review%20of%20complaints%20that%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengths%20that%20some%20air%20traffic%20controllers%20have%20gone%20through%20to%20maintain%20their%20jobs%20reflects%20the%20tediousness%20that%20the%20role%20demands%2C%20as%20they%20are%20the%20safeguards%20for%20the%20lives%20of%20millions%20upon%20millions%20of%20travelers.%20It%20is%20because%20of%20their%20work%20that%20passenger%20air%20travel%20in%20the%20US%20remains%20incredibly%20safe%2C%20a%20marvel%20of%20modern%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20Times%20report%20from%20September%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F21%2Fbusiness%2Fairline-safety-close-calls.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20close%20calls%20at%20US%20airports%20have%20occurred%20at%20a%20greater%20rate%20than%20previously%20known.%20An%20examination%20of%20internal%20FAA%20records%20by%20the%20newspaper%20revealed%20that%20in%202023%20such%20incidents%20took%20place%20multiple%20times%20a%20week.%20And%20the%20Times%20report%20also%20noted%20that%20in%20May%2C%20310%20of%20the%20313%20air%20traffic%20control%20facilities%20in%20the%20country%20had%20fewer%20than%20the%20recommended%20number%20of%20certified%20controllers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20safety%20issues%20don't%20just%20extend%20to%20the%20well-being%20of%20controllers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F08%2F27%2Ffaa-pilots-health-conditions-va-benefits%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20in%20August%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20federal%20authorities%20have%20been%20investigating%20roughly%205%2C000%20pilots%20who%20may%20have%20altered%20their%20medical%20records%20to%20withhold%20health%20issues%20that%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffaa-investigating-pilots-suspicion-major-health-issues-flying-veterans-benefits-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejeopardize%20their%20ability%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fly%20airplanes%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20air%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20the%20coping%20mechanisms%20that%20some%20of%20them%20have%20sought%20to%20employ%20were%20further%20detailed%20in%20complaints%20to%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20controllers%20in%20one%20air%20traffic%20facility%20were%20reported%20for%20%26quot%3Busing%20alcohol%20and%20illegal%20drugs%20while%20on%20position%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20were%20directing%20plane%20traffic%2C%20per%20a%20complaint%20examined%20by%20The%20Times.%20Another%20complaint%20listed%20the%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20odor%20of%20alcohol%26quot%3B%20that%20came%20from%20some%20controllers.%20Several%20controllers%20said%20that%20they%20witnessed%20some%20colleagues%20%26quot%3Bshowing%20extreme%20signs%20of%20mental%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20according%20to%20one%20FAA%20complaint%20reviewed%20by%20The%20Times%2C%20a%20controller%20said%20that%20she%20ingested%20up%20to%20nine%20vodka%20drinks%20per%20night%20to%20combat%20sleeping%20issues%20and%20panic%20attacks%20that%20a%20physician%20indicated%20was%20partly%20brought%20on%20by%20the%20stress%20of%20her%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFAA%20spokeswoman%20Jeannie%20Shiffer%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20The%20Times%20said%20that%20the%20agency%20%26quot%3Bmaintains%20the%20safest%2C%20most%20complex%20and%20busiest%20airspace%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20nation%20absolutely%20needs%20more%20air%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20and%20growing%20the%20work%20force%20will%20result%20in%20better%20working%20conditions%20and%20more%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShiffer%20also%20said%20that%20the%20agency%20prioritized%20the%20health%20of%20its%20air%20traffic%20controllers%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20provided%20free%20counseling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20have%20issues%2C%20we%20work%20with%20them%20to%20resolve%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controllers-workload-stress-alcohol-drugs-faa-close-calls-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701556386000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656ba7cb58e7c0c29a29079c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controllers-workload-stress-alcohol-drugs-faa-close-calls-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20air%20traffic%20controller%20workforce%20has%20been%20severely%20stretched%2C%20with%20staffing%20shortages%20leading%20to%20strenuous%20workweeks%20and%20alcohol%20or%20drug%20abuse.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20L.%20Dorman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-controllers-workload-stress-alcohol-drugs-faa-close-calls-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%2