EAdnoc%2C%20Saudi%20Aramco%2C%20ExxonMobil%2C%20Shell%20and%20other%20international%20oil%20majors%20signed%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECatherine%20Boudreau%20reported%20from%20Dubai%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20and%20Erin%20Snodgrass%20reported%20from%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellites-locate-source-of-methane-leaks-to-fight-climate-crisis-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESatellites%20are%20the%20next%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20hold%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20accountable%20in%20their%20promise%20to%20cut%20methane%20emissions%20and%20slow%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20host%20of%20this%20year's%20UN%20climate%20summit%20COP28%2C%20on%20Saturday%20announced%20that%20dozens%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20accounting%20for%2040%25%20of%20global%20production%20%E2%80%94%20aim%20to%20nearly%20eliminate%20their%20methane%20emissions%20by%202030.%20Many%20state-owned%20oil%20companies%20signed%20on%2C%20including%20the%20UAE's%20Adnoc%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20Saudi%20Aramco.%20US%20firms%20ExxonMobil%20and%20Shell%2C%20and%20other%20international%20oil%20majors%20will%20also%20participate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%2C%20a%20separate%20initiative%20was%20announced%20that%20will%20use%20satellites%20to%20track%20whether%20the%20companies%20keep%20their%20promise.%20The%20billionaire%20businessman%20and%20philanthropist%20Michael%20Bloomberg%20pledged%20%2440%20million%20to%20the%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20a%20partnership%20with%20the%20Environmental%20Defense%20Fund%20that%20will%20launch%20its%20own%20satellite%20early%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOil%20and%20gas%20companies%20often%20don't%20have%20the%20data%20on%20these%20methane%20emissions%2C%20including%20where%20leaks%20are%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloomberg%2C%20UN%20special%20envoy%20for%20climate%20ambition%20and%20solutions%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20Dubai.%20%26quot%3BEven%20when%20data%20is%20available%2C%20there%20often%20aren't%20rules%20and%20incentives%20in%20place%20to%20make%20sure%20companies%20do%20something%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMethane%20is%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%20with%2080%20times%20the%20warming%20power%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20though%20it%20only%20lingers%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20for%20about%20a%20decade%20compared%20with%20centuries%20for%20carbon%20dioxide.%20That%20short%20lifespan%20is%20why%20climate%20scientists%20say%20eliminating%20methane%20emissions%20is%20one%20of%20the%20quickest%20ways%20to%20slow%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-methane-tracker-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eis%20responsible%20for%2040%25%20of%20human-caused%20methane%20emissions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20leaking%20wells%2C%20compression%20stations%2C%20and%20pipelines%2C%20as%20well%20as%20by%20routinely%20burning%20off%20excess%20gas%20in%20a%20practice%20known%20as%20venting%20and%20flaring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20numerous%20countries%20and%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20have%20pledged%20to%20slash%20methane%20emissions%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20they%20are%20still%20rising%20to%20record%20levels%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-methane-tracker-2023%2Foverview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20IEA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20agency%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsalatainstitute.harvard.edu%2Fquantifying-methane-to-the-sky-and-beyond%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCompelled%2520by%2520Sargent%2520and%2520Budney%2527s%2CU.S.%2520Environmental%2520Protection%2520Agency%2527s%2520inventories.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Euniversity%20scientists%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.edf.org%2Fclimate%2Fmethane-studies%23%3A~%3Atext%3DExtensive%2520research%2520led%2520by%2520EDF%2Cthan%2520the%2520government%2527s%2520estimate%2520suggests.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenvironmental%20groups%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20published%20research%20showing%20that%20national%20governments%20are%20significantly%20undercounting%20total%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20measuring%20methane%20was%20challenging%20because%20the%20gas%20is%20colorless%2C%20leaks%20are%20unpredictable%2C%20and%20finding%20them%20involved%20expensive%20field%20studies%20with%20aircraft%20and%20handheld%20infrared%20cameras.%20That%20approach%20only%20offered%20a%20snapshot%20in%20time%20and%20the%20research%20took%20a%20long%20time%20to%20publish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20methods%20have%20changed%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%20A%20new%20generation%20of%20satellites%20can%20now%20pinpoint%20methane%20leaks%20almost%20anywhere%20and%2C%20within%20days%2C%20computers%20equipped%20with%20AI%20models%20can%20calculate%20the%20amount%20of%20emissions%20escaping.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20means%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20responsible%20for%20the%20plumes%20can%20be%20notified%20faster%20and%20potentially%20take%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20last%20year%20launched%20its%20own%20methane%20alert%20and%20response%20system%20that%20uses%20satellites%20to%20monitor%20emissions%20and%20notify%20countries%20and%20companies.%20Since%20then%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fnews-and-stories%2Fpress-release%2Funs-global-methane-tracking-system-set-translate-data-revolution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E1%2C500%20methane%20plumes%20were%20identified%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20some%20governments%20took%20action%2C%20including%20Argentina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2050%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20that%20signed%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecarbonization%20charter%26quot%3B%20on%20Saturday%20in%20Dubai%20agreed%20to%20eliminate%20routine%20flaring%2C%20improve%20the%20way%20they%20monitor%20methane%20leaks%2C%20and%20report%20progress%20on%20reducing%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOP28%20President%20Sultan%20Al%20Jaber%2C%20who%20also%20heads%20Adnoc%2C%20during%20a%20speech%20on%20Saturday%20said%20that%20tackling%20methane%20emissions%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20quick%20and%20easy%20win.%26quot%3B%20Adnoc%20earlier%20this%20year%20already%20promised%20to%20zero-out%20the%20pollutant%20by%202030%2C%20even%20as%20it%20plans%20to%20expand%20oil%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22COP28%20President%20Sultan%20Al%20Jaber%20walks%20through%20the%20venue%20ahead%20of%20the%20UN%20Climate%20Summit%20in%20Dubai%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65685d9586933e8fdb2e3fe8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECOP28%20President%20Sultan%20Al%20Jaber%20at%20the%20UN%20Climate%20Summit%20in%20Dubai%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Dejong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20companies%20deliver%2C%20we%20calculate%20it%20means%20reducing%20methane%20emission%20by%2080%25%20to%2090%25%2C%20which%20is%20critical%2C%26quot%3B%20EDF%20President%20Fred%20Krupp%20told%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that%20only%20happens%20if%20there's%20accountability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20satellite%20being%20launched%20by%20EDF%2C%20known%20as%20MethaneSAT%2C%20can%20regularly%20monitor%20methane%20emissions%20from%20regions%20accounting%20for%20much%20of%20the%20world's%20oil%20and%20gas%20production.%20That%20includes%20emerging%20and%20developing%20economies%2C%20where%20state-owned%20oil%20companies%20have%20been%20largely%20absent%20from%20methane%20pledges%20until%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20gathered%20by%20satellites%20can%20also%20help%20climate%20advocates%20push%20governments%20to%20implement%20tougher%20methane%20laws.%20EDF%20and%20Bloomberg%20Philanthropies%20are%20working%20with%20the%20IEA%2C%20UN%2C%20and%20the%20climate%20nonprofit%20RMI%20on%20its%20accountability%20push.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20EPA's%20'super%20emitter'%20program%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20European%20Union%20are%20already%20cracking%20down%20on%20methane%20emissions.%20The%20US%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fnewsreleases%2Fbiden-harris-administration-finalizes-standards-slash-methane-pollution-combat-climate%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEPA%2527s%2520final%2520rule%2520leverages%2520the%2Cthe%2520power%2520sector%2520in%25202021.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20Saturday%20finalized%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20reduce%20an%20estimated%2058%20million%20tons%20of%20methane%20emissions%20over%20the%20next%2015%20years.%20That%20figure%20is%20comparable%20to%20the%20emissions%20released%20by%20the%20entire%20US%20power%20sector%20in%202021%2C%20the%20agency%20said.%20The%20rules%20require%20companies%20to%20monitor%20leaks%2C%20limit%20flaring%20at%20oil%20wells%2C%20and%20reduce%20emissions%20from%20equipment%20like%20pumps%20and%20storage%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20emitter%26quot%3B%20program%20will%20allow%20certain%20third%20parties%20that%20detect%20large%20methane%20plumes%20to%20submit%20data%20to%20EPA%2C%20which%20will%20do%20its%20own%20verification%20before%20notifying%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20company%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20methane%20that%20will%20be%20captured%2C%20rather%20than%20released%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20heat%207.8%20millions%20homes%20this%20winter%2C%20EPA%20officials%20said%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20Friday.%20Once%20fully%20implemented%2C%20the%20rule%20will%20prevent%20the%20emissions%20of%20the%20equivalent%20of%201.5%20billion%20metric%20tons%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%20in%20November%20agreed%20to%20its%20first-ever%20law%20directing%20fossil%20fuel%20companies%20to%20measure%20and%20report%20their%20methane%20emissions%2C%20and%20bans%20most%20flaring%20and%20venting%20by%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20EU%20are%20part%20of%20the%20Global%20Methane%20Pledge%20that%20calls%20for%20a%2030%25%20reduction%20in%20methane%20emissions%20by%202030.%20At%20least%20155%20countries%20have%20signed%20the%20pledge%2C%20which%20launched%20in%202021%20at%20the%20UN%20climate%20summit%20in%20Glasgow%2C%20Scotland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20China%20and%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20the%20top%20two%20producers%20of%20methane%20emissions%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20signatories.%20China%20in%20November%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-unveils-action-plan-reduce-methane-emissions-2023-11-07%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epublished%20its%20own%20plan%20to%20reduce%20the%20pollutant%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20include%20any%20hard%20targets.%20The%20country's%20state-owned%20oil%20companies%20are%20also%20absent%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Bdecabonization%20charter%26quot%3B%20announced%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelanie%20Robinson%2C%20global%20climate%20program%20director%20at%20the%20World%20Resources%20Institute%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20methane%20commitments%20were%20encouraging%20but%20require%20strong%20measures%20to%20hold%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector%20still%20isn't%20being%20held%20accountable%20for%20all%20the%20emissions%20created%20by%20the%20fuel%20they%20sell%20to%20other%20industries.%20That's%20akin%20to%20a%20cigarette%20maker%20%26quot%3Bclaiming%20no%20responsibility%20for%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20product%20once%20it%20leaves%20the%20factory%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20Robinson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20voluntary%20promises%20alone%20won't%20acheive%20global%20climate%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcop28-un-climate-conference-oil-and-gas-methane-emissions-satellites-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701533089000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656b515d58e7c0c29a290565%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcop28-un-climate-conference-oil-and-gas-methane-emissions-satellites-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Michael%20Bloomberg%20pledged%20%2440%20million%20to%20a%20new%20climate%20initiative%20that%20will%20use%20satellites%20to%20ensure%2050%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20are%20cutting%20methane%20emissions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau%2CErin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcop28-un-climate-conference-oil-and-gas-methane-emissions-satellites-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Walmart%20joins%20the%20growing%20list%20of%20major%20companies%20to%20suspend%20advertising%20on%20Elon%20Musk's%20X%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226072%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20photo%20illustration%2C%20logo%20of%20'xAI'%20is%20displayed%20on%20a%20mobile%20phone%20screen%20near%20Elon%20Musk's%20photo%20in%20Ankara%2C%20Turkiye%20on%20November%207%2C%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656b19cb47f9ecb37d895d6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20been%20facing%20criticism%2C%20including%20from%20Tesla%20investors%2C%20for%20endorsing%20an%20antisemitic%20post%20on%20X.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWalmart%20has%20joined%20the%20growing%20list%20of%20companies%20suspending%20their%20ads%20on%20X.%C2%A0%C2%A