Famp_articleshow%2F105683629.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Badlega%20Raj%20ya%20Rivaaz'%3A%20Will%20Rajasthan%20Change%20its%20Government%20or%20the%20Pattern%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F05135822%2FF-GbtyzW0AACY5S.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20biggest%20question%20that%20dominated%20most%20debates%20and%20discussions%20on%20the%202023%20Rajasthan%20assembly%20polls%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ebadlega%20raj%20ya%20rivaaz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20essentially%20means%20whether%20the%20poll%20outcome%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20change%20of%20government%20or%20custom.%20Over%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20Rajasthan%20has%20had%20a%20history%20of%20voting%20out%20incumbents%20every%20five%20years.%20Anti-incumbency%20sentiments%20run%20high%20during%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20assembly%20polls%2C%20leading%20to%20tactical%20alignments%20of%20caste%20and%20community%20groups%20that%20make%20voting%20out%20the%20incumbent%20governments%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20342px)%2085vw%2C%20342px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22342%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-300x248.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-1024x845.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681756%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22282%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20time%20around%2C%20Rajasthan%20witnessed%20a%20different%20mood%2C%20even%20as%20historical%20precedents%20were%20stacked%20against%20the%20Ashok%20Gehlot-led%20Congress%20government.%20A%20range%20of%20social%20security%20schemes%20initiated%20by%20the%20Gehlot%20government%2C%20particularly%20the%20Chiranjeevi%2C%20a%20state-sponsored%20health%20insurance%20scheme%20up%20to%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20that%20covers%20most%20complex%20ailments%20and%20treatments%2C%20appeared%20to%20hold%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20good%20stead.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Importantly%2C%20most%20of%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20welfare%20measures%2C%20like%20increasing%20minimum%20wages%2C%20old%20age%20pension%2C%20subsidy%20in%20LPG%20cylinders%2C%20and%20scholarships%2C%20gave%20long-term%20relief%20to%20people%2C%20contrasting%20that%20of%20other%20state%20governments%20that%20have%20largely%20relied%20on%20delivering%20cash%20hand-outs%20to%20different%20sections%20of%20the%20electorate.%20Most%20pre-poll%20surveys%20showed%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20people%20preferred%20Gehlot%20over%20others%20as%20the%20chief%20minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20his%20spending%20on%20social%20welfare%20gave%20him%20little%20room%20to%20focus%20on%20infrastructure%20development%20and%20employment.%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20principal%20rival%20in%20the%20state%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20thus%2C%20concentrated%20on%20highlighting%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20failures%20on%20these%20fronts%2C%20apart%20from%20largely%20relying%20on%20its%20Hindutva%20and%20anti-corruption%20rhetoric.%20The%20BJP%20canvassed%20against%20Gehlot%20for%20his%20alleged%20failure%20to%20contain%20crimes%20against%20women%20and%20frequent%20paper%20leaks%20in%20entrance%20examinations%20conducted%20for%20government%20jobs.%20Above%20all%2C%20it%20amplified%20its%20allegation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cminority%20appeasement%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20Congress%20by%20regularly%20drawing%20focus%20on%20the%20brutal%20killing%20of%20Udaipur%20tailor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fudaipur-kanhaiya-lal-letters-nia-probe%5C%22%3EKanhaiya%20Lal%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20two%20Islamists.%20Even%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20pulled%20all%20the%20stops%20to%20talk%20about%20Kanhiaya%20Lal%E2%80%99s%20murder%20in%20most%20of%20his%20election%20speeches.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20parties%2C%20however%2C%20were%20pulled%20back%20by%20their%20own%20organisational%20problems.%20The%20BJP%20could%20not%20project%20a%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20face%2C%20amidst%20the%20ongoing%20feud%20between%20the%20Modi-Shah%20duo%20and%20former%20chief%20minister%20and%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tallest%20leader%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Vasundhara%20Raje%20Scindia.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20was%20torn%20between%20selecting%20its%20cadres%20and%20Scindia%E2%80%99s%20loyalists%20while%20distributing%20its%20election%20tickets%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20a%20number%20of%20rebels%20ended%20up%20challenging%20the%20official%20BJP%20candidates%20in%20a%20substantial%20number%20of%20seats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%2C%20too%2C%20had%20to%20face%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20long-drawn%20rivalry%20between%20Gehlot%20and%20the%20second-most%20important%20party%20leader%20Sachin%20Pilot.%20Although%20Congress%20president%20Malliakarjun%20Kharge%20engineered%20a%20last-minute%20truce%20between%20the%20two%2C%20by%20allowing%20both%20leaders%20to%20pick%20their%20candidates%20in%20their%20strongholds%2C%20the%20move%20seemed%20more%20like%20a%20damage-control%20exercise%20than%20an%20attempt%20at%20consolidation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F20120637%2F2022_12img19_Dec_2022_PTI12_19_2022_000246B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F20120637%2F2022_12img19_Dec_2022_PTI12_19_2022_000246B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F20120637%2F2022_12img19_Dec_2022_PTI12_19_2022_000246B-300x173.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F20120637%2F2022_12img19_Dec_2022_PTI12_19_2022_000246B-1024x590.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-633291%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22691%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20with%20party%20President%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20and%20Rajasthan%20CM%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20and%20others%20at%20a%20public%20meeting%20during%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%2C%20in%20Alwar%2C%20Monday%2C%20Dec.%2019%2C%202022.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdding%20to%20the%20mix%20of%20such%20complications%20was%20a%20third%20front%20led%20by%20Jat%20leader%20Hanuman%20Beniwal%E2%80%99s%20Rashtriya%20Loktantrik%20Party%20and%20Dalit%20leader%20Chandrashekhar%20Aazad%E2%80%99s%20Azad%20Samaj%20Party%20which%20may%20turn%20the%20largely%20bi-polar%20contest%20into%20a%20triangular%20fight%20in%20many%20pockets.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Adivasi%20Party%2C%20a%20faction%20that%20emerged%20out%20of%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Bharatiya%20Tribal%20Party%2C%20may%20play%20a%20spoiler%20for%20both%20the%20national%20parties%2C%20especially%20in%20Adivasi-dominated%20regions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrecisely%20because%20of%20such%20factors%20at%20play%2C%20political%20observers%20felt%20that%20Rajasthan%20saw%20not%20one%20but%20200%20elections%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20fierce%20localised%20battles%20between%20candidates%20in%20each%20of%20the%20200%20seats.%20The%20lack%20of%20a%20wave%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20party%20combined%20with%20factors%20like%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20own%20state-wide%20popularity%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20chief%20ministerial%20face%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20a%20hung%20outcome%20%E2%80%93%20a%20mandate%20that%20is%20more%20or%20less%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20perceived%20popularity%20or%20disapproval%20of%20candidates%20in%20every%20constituency.%20Anti-incumbency%20against%20sitting%20MLAs%20of%20both%20parties%20could%20become%20the%20most%20crucial%20element%20in%20the%202023%20assembly%20polls.%20All%20exit%20polls%2C%20too%2C%20have%20predicted%20a%20close%20contest.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20outcome%20is%20awaited%20on%20December%203%2C%20it%20will%20be%20significant%20how%20both%20the%20national%20parties%20perform%20in%20various%20regions%20%E2%80%93%20Marwar%20(61%20seats)%2C%20Shekhawati%20(21)%2C%20Dhundar%20(58)%2C%20Hadouti%20(17)%2C%20and%20Mewar%20(43).%20In%202018%2C%20Dhundar%20and%20Shekhawati%20regions%20had%20an%20unassailable%20lead%20to%20the%20Congress%20in%20what%20was%20a%20closely%20fought%20election.%20Historically%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20a%20distinct%20advantage%20over%20the%20Congress%20in%20Rajasthan.%20The%20saffron%20party%20has%20a%20greater%20social%20pool%20than%20the%20Congress%20from%20where%20it%20draws%20its%20support%2C%20because%20of%20which%20even%20when%20it%20is%20defeated%2C%20it%20ends%20up%20with%20a%20respectable%20tally.%20The%20Congress%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20crashes%20in%20electoral%20losses%2C%20like%20it%20did%20in%202013%20when%20it%20won%20merely%2021%20seats%20compared%20to%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20163.%20The%20BJP%20in%202008%20and%202018%20when%20it%20lost%20got%2078%20and%2073%20compared%20to%20Congress%E2%80%99s%2096%20and%20100%20respectively.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20vote%20shares%2C%20too%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20a%20similar%20advantage%2C%20almost%20always%20hovering%20around%20the%2040%25%20mark%20irrespective%20of%20the%20outcome%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20has%20swung%20between%2033%25%20to%2038%25.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20no%20one%20would%20have%20thought%20that%20the%20Congress%20could%20bring%20it%20this%20close%20but%20how%20Gehlot%20transformed%20the%202023%20assembly%20polls%20into%20a%20tightly-fought%20election%20is%20remarkable.%20Irrespective%20of%20the%20outcome%2C%20his%20long-term%20welfare%20policies%20will%20surely%20become%20a%20political%20template%20for%20the%20Congress%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20If%20Gehlot%20edges%20past%20the%20BJP%2C%20it%20will%20surely%20be%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Rajasthan%20as%20then%20the%20incumbent%20chief%20minister%20would%20have%20defeated%20not%20merely%20the%20BJP%20but%20also%20historical%20precedents%20but%20also%20structural%20factors%20stacked%20against%20his%20party.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20key%20constituencies%20to%20look%20out%20for%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESardarpura%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20has%20held%20this%20seat%20since%201998.%20He%20defeated%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Shambhu%20SIngh%20in%202018%20by%20securing%2063%25%20votes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETonk%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20Congress%20leader%20Sachin%20Pilot%20is%20seeking%20a%20reelection%20here%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Ajit%20Singh%20Mehta.%20He%20defeated%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Yoonus%20Khan%20by%2054%2C%20179%20votes%20in%202018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJhalrapatan%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20BJP%20leader%20Vasundhara%20Raje%20Scindia%20has%20been%20the%20legislator%20of%20the%20constituency%20since%202003.%20She%20secured%2054%25%20votes%20to%20defeat%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Manvendra%20Singh%2C%20son%20of%20former%20BJP%20union%20minister%20Manvendra%20Singh%2C%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUdaipur%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20A%20BJP%20stronghold%20but%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20national%20spokesperson%20Gourav%20Vallabh%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20here%20has%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20seat%20to%20watch%20out%20for.%20He%20is%20contesting%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Tarachand%20Jain%2C%20who%20is%20contesting%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20The%20seat%20was%20held%20multiple%20times%20by%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Gulab%20Chand%20Kataria%2C%20now%20the%20Assam%20governor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETijara%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20seat%20saw%20an%20extremely%20polarising%20campaign%20along%20religious%20lines%2C%20fuelled%20by%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Baba%20Balaknath.%20The%20saffron-clad%20leader%20and%20Alwar%20MP%20Balaknath%2C%20a%20follower%20of%20Nath%20Sampradaya%2C%20is%20seen%20by%20his%20supporters%20as%20the%20next%20BJP%20chief%20minister%20of%20Rajasthan.%20He%20is%20pitched%20against%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Imran%20Khan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJhotwara%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%20has%20fielded%20former%20union%20minister%20and%20Olympian%20Rajyavardhan%20Singh%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3ERathore%20here.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChuru%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%20veteran%20Rajendra%20Rathore%20is%20facing%20a%20tough%20battle%20here.%20Rathore%2C%20too%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20probables%20for%20the%20top%20chair%20in%20case%20of%20a%20win%20for%20the%20BJP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELachhmangarh%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20The%20state%20Congress%20chief%20Govind%20Singh%20Dotasara%20has%20been%20the%20MLA%20here%20since%202008.%20A%20prominent%20Jat%20leader%20of%20the%20state%2C%20Dotasara%20also%20faced%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20raids%20in%20a%20case%20related%20to%20paper%20leaks%20in%20entrance%20exams%20during%20the%20election%20campaign.%20He%20is%20up%20against%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Subhash%20Meheria.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAmber%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20Former%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20state%20president%20and%20Jat%20leader%20Satish%20Poonia%20is%20contesting%20here%20against%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Prashant%20Sharma.%20Poonia%20had%20defeated%20Sharma%20in%202018%20by%20over%2013000%20votes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701531921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F05135822%2FF-GbtyzW0AACY5S.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbadlega-raj-ya-rivaaz-will-rajasthan-change-its-government-or-the-pattern%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22States%20known%20to%20always%20vote%20out%20the%20incumbent%20like%20Punjab%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Kerala%20have%20defied%20the%20norm%20in%202012%2C%202016%20and%202021%2C%20respectively.%20Which%20way%20will%20Rajasthan%20go%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbadlega-raj-ya-rivaaz-will-rajasthan-change-its-government-or-the-pattern%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LIC%20amends%20norms%20for%20inclusion%20of%20shareholders'%20directors%20on%20its%20board%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701531634000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-11%2F23%2Ffull%2F1700736727-4867.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flic-amends-norms-for-inclusion-of-shareholders-directors-on-its-board-123120200776_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20present%2C%20LIC%20has%20five%20executive%20directors%2C%20including%20Chairman%20Siddhartha%20Mohanty%2C%20nine%20independent%20directors%20and%20one%20government%20nominee%20Director%20MP%20Tangirala%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flic-amends-norms-for-inclusion-of-shareholders-directors-on-its-board-123120