%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123906%2FF8oD1roWcAAOHje.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123906%2FF8oD1roWcAAOHje-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19123906%2FF8oD1roWcAAOHje-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680774%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMadhya%20Pradesh%20Congress%20leaders%20release%20party%20manifesto%20on%20October%2017%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40OfficeOfKNath%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20political%20fate%20of%20incumbent%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%2C%20who%20helmed%20the%20state%20government%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20is%20at%20stake.%20So%20is%20the%20success%20or%20failure%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20experiment%20with%20a%20collective%20leadership%20to%20dilute%20cumulative%20anti-incumbency%20in%20a%20state%20where%20it%20has%20ruled%20continuously%20since%202003%2C%20barring%20a%2015-month%20gap%20in%202018-2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20result%20would%20be%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20political%20clout%20of%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%2C%20who%20had%20engineered%20the%20rebellion%20of%20several%20MLAs%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20Congress%20government%20in%202020%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20acceptability%20of%20the%2077-year-old%20Kamal%20Nath%20as%20the%20declared%20chief%20ministerial%20face%20of%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20given%20the%20long%20and%20deep%20association%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20political%20ancestor%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20with%20MP%2C%20the%20results%20on%20December%203%2C%20seen%20together%20with%20the%20verdict%20of%202018%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20saffron%20party%20lost%20power%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202003%20%E2%80%93%20would%20provide%20us%20a%20glimpse%20of%20shifting%20sands%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifth%2C%20the%20success%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20promise%20of%20drastically%20changing%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20common%20voter%20would%20be%20tested%20in%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20most%20backward%20states%20with%20a%20high%20population%20of%20marginalised%20Hindu%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20him%20leading%20the%20charge%20as%20the%20main%20face%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20overshadowing%20the%20outgoing%20chief%20minister%2C%20the%20result%20would%20also%2C%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20be%20a%20reflection%20on%20his%20leadership%20and%20popularity%2C%20although%20in%20case%20of%20an%20adverse%20result%20the%20BJP%20is%20expected%20to%20shield%20him%20from%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F03105424%2FScreenshot-2023-10-03-at-10.53.5.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F03105424%2FScreenshot-2023-10-03-at-10.53.5.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F03105424%2FScreenshot-2023-10-03-at-10.53.5-300x154.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F03105424%2FScreenshot-2023-10-03-at-10.53.5-1024x525.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677981%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22615%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPM%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20Gwalior%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20on%20October%202.%20Photo%3A%20Video%20screengrab%2FX%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strong%20anti-incumbency%20wave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Congress%20hopes%20to%20repeat%2C%20or%20even%20better%20its%202018%20performance%2C%20when%20it%20won%20114%20seats%20in%20the%20230-member%20Assembly%2C%20the%20BJP%20faces%20the%20task%20of%20protecting%20one%20of%20its%20strongest%20political%20and%20ideological%20bastions%20in%20the%20entire%20country.%20Travelling%20in%20the%20state%2C%20beneath%20the%20maze%20of%20grievances%20and%20assertions%2C%20there%20were%20two%20dominant%20streams%20of%20thought%20among%20voters.%20There%20were%20those%20who%20appreciated%20the%20work%20done%20by%20the%20Chouhan-led%20BJP%20government%20since%202005%20and%20still%20trusted%20Modi%20as%20the%20supreme%20leader.%20The%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20long-standing%20link%20with%20Hindutva%20ideology%2C%20its%20organisational%20structure%2C%20welfare%20programs%2C%20particularly%20for%20women%2C%20financial%20support%2C%20and%20infrastructural%20development%20encouraged%20loyalty%20to%20the%20saffron%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatched%20against%20this%20was%20a%20solid%20and%20discernible%20sentiment%20of%20anti-incumbency%2C%20built%20on%20frustration%20over%20unemployment%2C%20inflation%2C%20unsatisfactory%20crop%20prices%2C%20repeated%20corruption%20allegations%2C%20scams%20obstructing%20recruitment%20to%20government%20jobs%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20boredom%20and%20fatigue%20with%20the%20way%20the%20state%20has%20been%20running%20under%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%2C%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20recognised%20its%20deficiencies%20as%20it%2C%20instead%20of%20selling%20the%20work%20done%20by%20it%20in%20the%20last%20tenure%2C%20desperately%20referred%20to%20the%20past%2C%20underlining%20the%20comparative%20change%20it%20brought%20about%20in%20the%20state%20over%20the%20two%20decades%20%E2%80%93%20the%20journey%20from%20%3Cem%3Ebimaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20%3Cem%3Ebemisaal%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-congress-has-an-edge-over-bjp-in-madhya-pradesh%5C%22%3EWhy%20Congress%20Has%20an%20Edge%20Over%20BJP%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20tribal%20dominated%20Dhar%20district%20in%20western%20MP%E2%80%99s%20Nimar%2C%20Phool%20Singh%2C%20a%20farmer%20who%20hails%20from%20the%20Bhilala%20tribe%2C%20was%20clear%20he%20wanted%20to%20give%20the%20Congress%20a%20chance%20to%20rule%20after%20two%20decades.%20The%20Congress%20promise%20of%20waiving%20off%20farm%20loans%2C%20reducing%20electricity%20bills%20and%20providing%20Rs%201%2C500%20stipend%20to%20women%20was%20a%20big%20catch%20in%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20dusty%20village%20in%20Manawar%20constituency.%20Sanju%2C%20a%20Bhilala%20woman%2C%20too%20wanted%20the%20Congress%20government%20as%20she%20felt%20that%20despite%20the%20long%20rule%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20educated%20youth%20in%20the%20state%20were%20unemployed.%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%20has%20changed%20sides%20in%20this%20election.%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20vote%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Raila%2C%20a%20Bhil%20farmer%2C%20who%20had%20previously%20supported%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20central%20MP%E2%80%99s%20Sehore%20district%2C%20Dalit%20farmer%20Sumer%20Singh%20fondly%20remembered%20the%20pre-2003%20Congress%20rule.%20He%20was%20unhappy%20with%20his%20stagnant%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20%E2%80%9Cendless%E2%80%9D%20inflation%20and%20rising%20costs%20of%20farming%2C%20uncertain%20rates%20for%20his%20%3Cem%3Etur%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20wheat%20crops%20and%20difficulty%20in%20procuring%20urea.%20%E2%80%9CEveryone%20is%20troubled%20by%20the%20BJP.%20Even%20the%20monsoon%20gods%20have%20stopped%20blessing%20us%20due%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20showcasing%20a%20hint%20of%20personal%20superstition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20substantial%20section%20of%20voters%20across%20caste%20and%20class%20expressed%20a%20negative%20sentiment%20against%20the%20Chouhan%20government%2C%20either%20based%20on%20fatigue%2C%20dissatisfaction%20or%20simply%20a%20desire%20for%20change%2C%20the%20saffron%20party%20still%20enjoyed%20a%20rock-solid%20base%20of%20committed%20voters%20in%20the%20central%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-300x194.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-1024x662.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684198%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22776%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBJP%20supporters%20hold%20up%20Modi%20posters.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Congress%20suppresses%20our%20Hindu%20brothers%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rahul%20Malviya%2C%20a%20driver%20in%20Sehore.%20When%20asked%20to%20count%20the%20achievements%20of%20the%20BJP%20government%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20provides%20us%20benefits%20from%20the%20moment%20we%20are%20born%20till%20we%20die.%20Then%20there%20is%20free%20ration.%20They%20also%20abrogated%20Article%20370%20%5Bin%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%5D%20and%20built%20the%20Ram%20Mandir.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Sagar%2C%20an%20OBC%20labourer%20Bharat%20Patel%2C%20though%20unsatisfied%20with%20the%20state%20government%2C%20felt%20he%20was%20obliged%20to%20vote%20for%20the%20BJP%20and%20Modi%20because%20of%20what%20they%20stood%20for.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20big%20discussion%20in%20my%20area%20about%20changing%20the%20government.%20I%E2%80%99m%20confused.%20My%20%3Cem%3Eaatma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(conscience)%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20me%20to%20vote%20against%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20even%20though%20the%20BJP%20lost%20the%20election%20to%20the%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20the%20BJP%20won%20109%20seats%20against%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20114%20%E2%80%93%20it%20secured%200.13%25%20more%20votes%2C%20showcasing%20its%20popular%20acceptance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20four%20elections%20in%20MP%20(2003%2C%202008%2C%202013%20and%202018)%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20in%20the%20state%20has%20been%2043%25%2C%2038%25%2C%2045%25%20and%2041%25%20as%20against%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%2032%25%2C%2032%25%2C%2036%25%20and%2041%25.%20Although%20the%20saffron%20party%20has%20occupied%20the%20dominant%20position%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20made%20consistent%20improvement%20which%20culminated%20in%20a%20remarkable%20jump%20in%202018%20when%20it%20formed%20government%20with%20the%20support%20of%20three%20opposition%20party%20MLAs%20and%20four%20independent%20legislators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20aspect%20of%20the%202018%20elections%20was%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20six%20percent%20vote%20share%20increase%20in%20the%20BJP-favoured%20territories%20of%20Madhya%20Bharat%20and%20Malwa%20North%2C%20noted%20political%20analyst%20Ashish%20Ranjan%20of%20%3Cem%3EDatalok.in%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20recent%20report.%20This%20gain%20translated%20into%2020%20additional%20seats%20for%20the%20Congress%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20election%2C%20indicating%20a%20deep%20incision%20into%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20stronghold%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20run%20by%20Kamal%20Nath%20could%20only%20last%2015%20months%20after%20the%20BJP%20engineered%20mass%20defections%20in%20the%20Congress%20and%20snatched%20the%20reins%20from%20it%20in%202020.%20The%20defeat%20in%202018%20and%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20he%20returned%20to%20power%20in%202020%20had%20already%20reduced%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20stature.%20The%20way%20in%20which%20he%20was%20sidelined%20by%20the%20BJP%20in%20its%20campaign%20%E2%80%93%20by%20not%20declaring%20him%20as%20the%20official%20chief%20ministerial%20candidate%20%E2%80%93%20has%20raised%20several%20questions%20on%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20political%20future.%20Whether%20the%20BJP%20loses%20or%20wins%2C%20the%20result%20day%20is%20a%20day%20of%20reckoning%20for%20him%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EVM%20would%20not%20only%20settle%20the%20question%20whether%20Kamal%20Nath%20would%20get%20a%20second%20go%20at%20running%20a%20government%20but%20also%20provide%20us%20a%20glimpse%20of%20the%20battle%20for%20leadership%20within%20the%20BJP%20and%20how%20it%20approaches%20state%20elections%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20advantage%20of%20the%20BJP%20presenting%20a%20diverse%20front%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20fielding%20four%20MPs%2C%20three%20Union%20ministers%20%E2%80%93%20Narendra%20Singh%20Tomar%2C%20Faggan%20Singh%20Kulaste%20and%20Prahlad%20Patel%20%E2%80%93%20and%20one%20national%20general%20secretary%20Kailash%20Vijayvargiya%20in%20the%20Assembly%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20opted%20for%20a%20fresh%20experiment%20of%20projecting%20a%20collective%20leadership%20under%20Modi.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20campaign%20took%20pace%20and%20his%20rivals%20got%20caught%20up%20in%20their%20respective%20constituencies%20and%20controversies%2C%20Chouhan%20tried%20hard%20to%20reclaim%20his%20position%20through%20extensive%20campaigning%20and%20showcasing%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20collective%20leadership%20gambit%20in%20a%20state%20where%20it%20already%20had%20a%20popular%20face%2C%20an%20OBC%20to%20boot%2C%20had%20several%20elements%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20to%20provide%20options%20to%20voters%20disenchanted%20with%20Chouhan%20and%20looking%20for%20a%20fresh%20face%20to%20lead%20the%20government.%20Second%2C%20by%20fielding%20these%20leaders%2C%20who%20hail%20from%20different%20region%20and%20castes%2C%20the%20BJP%20sought%20to%20energise%20its%20cadre%20and%20tease%20voters%20across%20communities.%20This%20gave%20rise%20to%20the%20possibility%20that%20if%20the%20BJP%20won%2C%20it%20could%20provide%20a%20new%20chief%20minister%20from%20a%20particular%20caste.%20In%20a%20state%20with%20immense%20regional%20diversity%2C%20both%20politically%20and%20culturally%2C%20this%20tactic%2C%20in%20a%20tightly-fought%20battle%20could%20offset%20some%20loss%20or%20anti-incumbency.%20The%20third%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20collective%20leadership%20was%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20diminishing%20stature%2C%20under%20whose%20leadership%20the%20BJP%20lost%20in%202018.%20A%20new%20chief%20minister%20could%20provide%20BJP%20a%20fresh%20outlook%20and%20agenda%20in%20the%20state%20where%20it%20already%20enjoys%20a%20strong%20organisational%20strength%20and%20ideological%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-bjps-hindutva-campaign-is-not-working-in-madhya-pradesh%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Hindutva%20Card%20is%20Not%20Working%20for%20BJP%20in%20Poll-Bound%20Madhya%20Pradesh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20seized%20the%20initiative%20early-on%20as%20the%20saffron%20party%20trailed%20in%20the%20perception%20game%20for%20most%20of%20this%20year.%20The%20Congress%2C%20by%20causing%20defections%20of%20core%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20which%20coincided%20with%20a%20cloud%20of%20doubt%20hovering%20over%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20own%20future%2C%20appeared%20to%20be%20in%20the%20driving%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20declared%20a%20chief%20ministerial%20face%2C%20Kamal%20Nath%2C%20and%20pursued%20its%20successful%20strategy%20of%20winning%20over%20voters%20in%20Karnataka%20through%20welfare%20guarantees%20and%20deliverables%20linked%20to%20social%20security.%20The%20party%20also%20did%20well%20to%20keep%20under%20wraps%20any%20signs%20of%20infighting%20and%20consistently%20projected%20a%20collective%20front%20under%20Nath%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20The%20possible%20damage%20that%20the%20rebel%20candidates%20and%20disgruntled%20leaders%20may%20do%20to%20each%20party%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20and%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20on%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20tally%2C%20would%20only%20be%20revealed%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFacing%20an%20early%20onslaught%20and%20a%20united%20Congress%2C%20Chouhan%20tried%20to%20project%20a%20counter%20narrative%20by%20launching%20schemes%20such%20as%20Ladli%20Behna%20to%20woo%20women%20voters%20through%20monetary%20benefits.%20While%20the%20Ladli%20Behna%20scheme%20appeared%20to%20be%20popular%2C%20it%20was%20not%20enough%20for%20everyone.%20For%20some%2C%20it%20came%20too%20late.%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThey%20started%20this%20scheme%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20election.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20anything%20before%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rukmini%20Kushwaha%20in%20Indore.%20In%20a%20Dalit%20busty%20in%20Dewas%2C%20crippling%20inflation%20round-the-year%20and%20lack%20of%20overall%20improvement%20in%20life%20mattered%20more%20than%20monetary%20assistance.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20not%20received%20any%20toilet%20or%20%3Cem%3Epucca%3C%2Fem%3E%20house%20or%20water%20tank.%20Oil%20and%20tomatoes%20are%20priced%20like%20silver%20and%20gold%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Reena%2C%20a%20Dalit%20voter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Congress%20promised%20to%20conduct%20a%20caste%20census%20if%20voted%20to%20power%2C%20the%20result%20would%20also%20provide%20opportunity%20to%20both%20parties%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20counting%20of%20the%20OBC%20population%20in%20the%20build-up%20to%20the%20general%20election%20next%20year.%20However%2C%20on%20the%20surface%2C%20the%20caste%20census%20was%20not%20a%20big%20talking%20point%20among%20voters%2C%20with%20most%20of%20their%20concerns%20limited%20to%20livelihood%20issues%2C%20corruption%20and%20regional%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EJaisa%20chal%20raha%20hai%20chalne%20de%20sanatan%20dharm%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Let%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20and%20society%20function%20the%20way%20it%20is)%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kamal%20Rajak%2C%20an%20OBC%20farmer%20in%20Sagar%2C%20who%20despite%20wanting%20to%20change%20the%20government%20due%20to%20unemployment%2C%20believed%20a%20caste%20census%20would%20hurt%20the%20Hindu%20society.%20The%202023%20MP%20election%20result%20could%20possibly%20also%20impact%20the%20way%20the%20partners%20in%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20deal%20with%20each%20other%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20neighbouring%20state%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20which%20has%2080%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh-profile%20battle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20featured%20a%20number%20of%20high-profile%20and%20high-stake%20electoral%20battles%20involving%20top%20leaders%20from%20both%20parties%2C%20in%20particular%20the%20BJP%20which%20fielded%20several%20national-level%20heavyweights.In%20Budhni%2C%20Chouhan%20defended%20his%20fort%20against%20the%20Congress%20candidate%20Vikram%20Mastal%2C%20a%20TV%20actor-turned-politician%20known%20for%20playing%20the%20role%20of%20Hanuman%20in%20the%20serial%20Ramayan%20in%202008.%20Congress%20chief%20minsterial%20candidate%20Kamal%20Nath%20contested%20from%20Chhindwara%2C%20his%20political%20bastion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20leaders%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20also%20prospective%20chief%20minster%20candidates%2C%20were%20also%20in%20the%20fray%20this%20time.%20While%20Union%20agriculture%20minister%20Narendra%20Singh%20Tomar%20contested%20from%20Dimni%20against%20the%20sitting%20Congress%20MLA%20Ravindra%20Singh%20Tomar%20Bhidosa%2C%20another%20important%20Union%20minister%2C%20Prahlad%20Singh%20Patel%2C%20was%20fielded%20from%20Narsingpur%20constituency%20where%20he%20replaced%20the%20sitting%20MLA%20and%20his%20younger%20brother%20Jalam%20Singh%20Patel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETribal%20leader%20and%20Union%20minister%20Faggan%20Singh%20Kulaste%20contested%20from%20Niwas%20seat%20in%20Mandla.%20BJP%20general%20secretary%20Kailash%20Vijayvargiya%20was%20fielded%20in%20Indore-1%20against%20the%20popular%20Congress%20MLA%20Sanjay%20Shukla%20in%20one%20of%20the%20toughest%20battles%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20in%20the%20Datia%20constituency%20would%20also%20be%20well-watched%20as%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20and%20senior%20minister%20Narottam%20Mishra%2C%20a%20CM%20post%20hopeful%2C%20had%20narrowly%20won%20last%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20and%20leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20Govind%20Singh%20contested%20from%20Lahar%2C%20a%20seat%20he%20has%20held%20since%201990%2C%20in%20Raghogarh%20constituency%2C%20a%20seat%20never%20won%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20Jaivardhan%20Singh%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Congress%20veteran%20Digvijaya%20Singh%2C%20would%20look%20to%20repeat%20his%20success%20of%202013%20and%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contest%20in%20Hoshangabad%20seat%20also%20intrigued%20observers%20as%20the%20Congress%20fielded%20a%20BJP%20rebel%20and%20former%20legislator%20Girija%20Shankar%20Sharma%20against%20his%20brother%20and%20sitting%20BJP%20MLA%20Sitasharan%20Sharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701518596000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13192647%2FF0g9YnHagAEuCqI.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcan-disenchantment-and-fatigue-trump-an-18-year-old-bjp-record-in-madhya-pradesh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Opposition%20Congress%20seized%20the%20initiative%20early-on%20as%20the%20saffron%20party%20trailed%20in%20the%20perception%20game%20for%20most%20of%20this%20year.%20The%20Congress%2C%20by%20causing%20defections%20of%20key%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20which%20coincided%20with%20a%20cloud%20of%20doubt%20hovering%20over%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%20own%20future%2C%20appeared%20to%20be%20in%20the%20driving%20seat.%20But%20BJP%20has%20'made%20up'%20the%20gap%2C%20say%20others.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcan-disenchantment-and-fatigue-trump-an-18-year-old-bjp-record-in-madhya-pradesh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pannun%2C%20Nijjar%20and%20the%20Constant%20Need%20to%20find%20the%20'Enemies'%20of%20Modi's%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F26082650%2F33F81A3F-BCF6-4D05-975C-264958F029F4_1_105_c.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20quite%20possible%20that%20our%20ruling%20establishment%20may%20be%20able%20to%20persuade%20Washington%20not%20to%20make%20too%20much%20of%20the%20alleged%20Indian%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20United%20States%20citizen%2C%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%20on%20American%20soil.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20Americans%20have%2C%20for%20multiple%20reasons%2C%20put%20all%20their%20eggs%20in%20the%20Modi%20basket.%20In%20fact%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20the%20totally%20envious%20position%20of%20being%20the%20preferred%20choice%20of%20both%20Washington%20and%20Moscow%20for%20leadership%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20though%20for%20different%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20convergence%20of%20transactional%20calculations%20between%20Moscow%20and%20Washington%20may%20be%20found%20enormously%20satisfactory%20by%20the%20geopolitical%20elements%20of%20the%20ruling%20class%20in%20New%20Delhi%3B%20but%2C%20it%20would%20be%20comforting%20to%20believe%20that%20saner%20and%20sober%20citizens%20are%20finally%20coming%20to%20understand%20the%20enormous%20damage%20that%20the%20Modi%20persona%20has%20inflicted%20on%20the%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20community%20may%20choose%20to%20take%20at%20face%20value%20our%20official%20assertion%20that%20assassinations%20and%20hit%20jobs%20are%20not%20%E2%80%9Cour%20policy%E2%80%9D%20but%20vast%20sections%20of%20Indian%20society%20have%20experienced%20for%20themselves%20the%20liberties%20our%20ruling%20coterie%20has%20taken%20with%20norms%20and%20laws%20%E2%80%93%20all%20the%20while%20maintaining%20the%20fa%C3%A7ade%20of%20observed%20legalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2FPannun%20capers%20can%20only%20be%20understood%20as%20wages%20of%20%E2%80%9C56-inch-ism.%E2%80%9D%20%C2%A0Nine%20years%20ago%2C%20our%20otherwise%20surefooted%20strategic%20establishment%20fell%20for%20the%20mythology%20that%20had%20been%20crafted%20by%20the%20Modi%20crowd%20for%20capturing%20political%20power%3A%20that%20a%20weak%20and%20timid%20political%20leadership%20%5Bexemplified%20by%20the%20polite%20and%20soft-spoken%20Dr.%20Manmohan%20Singh%5D%20had%20held%20India%20back%20from%20achieving%20its%20potential%20for%20greatness.%20After%20decades%2C%20India%20now%20had%20a%20prime%20minister%20who%20was%20flaunting%20his%20physical%20agility%20and%20swagger%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20national%20power%20and%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01141008%2FPannun-FP.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01141008%2FPannun-FP.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01141008%2FPannun-FP-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01141008%2FPannun-FP-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01141008%2FPannun-FP-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687240%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40SFJGenCounsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20middle%20classes%2C%20especially%20those%20with%20a%20son%20or%20a%20daughter%20in%20North%20America%2C%20were%20the%20most%20eager%20suckers%20for%20this%20bravado.%20The%20tall%20talk%20of%20%E2%80%9Csorting%E2%80%9D%20out%20Pakistan%20or%20looking%20China%20straight%20in%20the%20eye%20was%20catnip%20to%20the%20masses.%20Big%20business%2C%20too%2C%20went%20along%20because%20this%20bluster%20meant%20India%20having%20to%20purchase%20or%20build%20more%20and%20more%20weapon%20systems.%20War-mongering%20has%20always%20been%20good%20for%20businessmen.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20generals%20and%20admirals%20were%20grinning%20from%20ear%20to%20ear%20too%3B%20here%20at%20last%20was%20a%20prime%20minister%20who%20understood%20the%20business%20of%20conflicts%20and%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20most%20cunning%20subscribers%20of%20this%20%E2%80%9C56-inch-ism%E2%80%9D%20were%20the%20overlords%20of%20the%20security%20establishment.%20These%20shadowy%20men%20quickly%20sized%20up%20our%20new%20saviour%2C%20decoded%20his%20insecurities%20and%20worked%20on%20his%20megalomania%3B%20they%20understood%20the%20great%20man%E2%80%99s%20need%20for%20%E2%80%9Cenemies%E2%80%9D%20to%20be%20tamed%20and%20vanquished.%20These%20%E2%80%9Csecurity-%20%3Cem%3Ewallahs%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20produced%20a%20whole%20roster%20of%20enemies%3A%20urban%20naxals%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctukde%20tukde%20gangs%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Kashmiris%2C%20the%20minorities%2C%20the%20farmers%2C%20the%20terrorists%2C%20the%20subversives%2C%20etc.%2C%20to%20be%20conquered%20and%20eliminated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthreat%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cunity%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cintegrity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20higher%20the%20level%20of%20threat%20that%20these%20enemies%20were%20deemed%20to%20be%20capable%20of%20making%20against%20India%20and%20its%20greatest%20saviour%2C%20the%20greater%20were%20the%20powers%20granted%20to%20all%20those%20institutions%20and%20agencies%20which%20deal%20in%20the%20currency%20of%20violence%20and%20intimidation%20and%20coercion.%20An%20appropriately%20impressed%20judiciary%20went%20along%20with%20the%20security%20crowd%E2%80%99s%20definitions%20and%20interpretations%20of%20the%20needs%20of%20national%20security.%20The%20judiciary%2C%20at%20least%20at%20the%20lower%20levels%2C%20was%20even%20prepared%20to%20put%20anyone%20in%20jail%20who%20dared%20to%20mock%20or%20ridicule%20the%20prime%20minister.%C2%A0%20His%20%E2%80%9Cimage%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cprestige%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdignity%E2%80%9D%20are%20now%20inextricably%20tied%20up%20with%20the%20defence%20and%20well-being%20of%20the%20realm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nijjar%2FPannun%20capers%20can%20be%20understood%20only%20in%20this%20demonology%2C%20crafted%20and%20scripted%20by%20cunning%20security%20managers.%20These%20crafty%20operatives%20felt%20enthused%20and%20empowered%20because%20their%20principal%20was%20equally%20adept%20at%20using%20the%20%E2%80%9Cenemies%E2%80%9D%20conjured%20up%20by%20them%20to%20tickle%20the%20average%20Hindu%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20insecurity.%20Having%20tamed%20the%20Muslims%20into%20submission%2C%20it%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20the%20Sikhs%20would%20get%20singled%20out%20as%20a%20source%20of%20new%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20those%20who%20live%20in%20Punjab%20will%20laugh%20at%20the%20suggestion%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CKhalistanis%E2%80%9D%20pose%20any%20kind%20of%20existential%20threat%20to%20India.%20There%20is%20no%20%E2%80%9CKhalistani%E2%80%9D%20constituency%20in%20Punjab.%20But%20the%20security%20managers%20know%20our%20political%20masters%E2%80%99%20need%20for%20%E2%80%9Cenemies%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthreats%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%2C%20by%20now%2C%20have%20become%20adept%20at%20weaving%20the%20Vishwaguru%20balderdash%20into%20their%20own%20empire-building%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Israel%20can%20go%20after%20its%20enemies%20beyond%20its%20borders%2C%20why%20can%E2%80%99t%20India%2C%20endowed%20as%20it%20is%20with%20decisive%20leadership%2C%20sort%20out%20those%20who%20dare%20to%20mock%20and%20challenge%20us%20from%20the%20safety%20of%20Canada%20or%20the%20United%20States%3F%20If%20American%20agents%20can%20take%20care%20of%20Iranian%20Commander%20Qassem%20Soleimani%2C%20we%20%C2%A0can%20at%20least%20finance%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejuggad%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20do%20in%20a%20Pannun.%20The%20political%20masters%20could%20not%20possibly%20object%2C%20as%20they%20knew%20how%20the%20Nijjar%20business%20was%20applauded%20in%20%E2%80%98nationalistic%E2%80%9D%20quarters%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20coming%20of%20age%20as%20a%20truly%20global%20player.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20over-reach%20was%20an%20inevitable%20downstream%20effect%20of%20the%20phony%2056-inch-ism.%20We%20miscalculate%20and%20over-talk%20and%20over-sell%20our%20limited%20capacities%20and%20mediocre%20competence%20just%20because%20we%20can%20gather%20a%20howling%20crowd%20in%20Houston%20or%20New%20York%20we%20allow%20ourselves%20to%20dream%20global%20dreams%20%E2%80%93%20and%20feel%20unapologetically%20good%20about%20our%20new%20%E2%80%9Cstature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Pannun%20business%20is%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20damage%20that%20bogus%20political%20masters%20have%20inflicted%20on%20the%20well-being%20of%20all%20our%20national%20institutions.%20Unrelenting%20aggression%20against%20political%20rivals%20and%20foes%20has%20now%20corroded%20the%20judgment%20and%20wisdom%20of%20all%20those%20empowered%20savants%20whose%20duty%20it%20is%20to%20safeguard%20the%20core%20of%20our%20nation%E2%80%99s%20abiding%20interests%20from%20the%20excesses%20of%20the%20petty%20demagogue.%20No%20%3Cem%3Eacche%20din%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fhkhare%5C%22%3EHarish%20Khare%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20editor-in-chief%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3EThe%20Tribune%3Ci%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701517602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F26082650%2F33F81A3F-BCF6-4D05-975C-264958F029F4_1_105_c.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fpannun-nijjar-and-the-constant-need-to-find-the-enemies-of-modis-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20most%20cunning%20subscribers%20of%20Modi's%20%E2%80%9C56-inch-ism%E2%80%9D%20were%20the%20overlords%20of%20the%20security%20establishment.%20These%20shadowy%20men%20quickly%20sized%20up%20our%20new%20saviour%20and%20understood%20the%20great%20man%E2%80%99s%20need%20for%20'enemies'%20to%20be%20tamed%20and%20vanquished.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fpannun-nijjar-and-the-constant-need-to-find-the-enemies-of-modis-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chennai-based%20Shrinithi%20Capital%20aims%20to%20double%20AUM%20to%20Rs%20600%20cr%20by%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701516023000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F05%2Ffull%2F1680674554-5502.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fchennai-based-shrinithi-capital-aims-to-double-aum-to-rs-600-cr-by-2024-123120200491_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Under%20the%20expansion%20plan%2C%20Shrinithi%20Capital%20aims%20to%20increase%20its%20branch%20network%20from%2050%20to%2080%2C%20extending%20operations%20to%20Kerala%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Karnataka%2C%20the%20statement%20added%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fchennai-based-shrinithi-capital-aims-to-double-aum-to-rs-600-cr-by-2024-123120200491_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fchennai-based-shrinithi-capital-aims-to-double-aum-to-rs-600-cr-by-2024-123120200491_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fchennai-based-shrinithi-capital-aims-to-double-aum-to-rs-600-cr-by-2024-123120200491_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Amrit%20Kaal%E2%80%99%3A%20Hunger%2C%20Inequity%20and%20a%20%2430-Trillion%20Economy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F13084433%2FIMG_1352.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20goes%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1980689%5C%22%3EPress%20Information%20Bureau%20(PIB)%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20on%2029%20November%2C%202023%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Cabinet%20led%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20decided%20that%20the%20Central%20government%20will%20provide%20free%20food%20grains%20to%20about%2081.35%20crore%20beneficiaries%20under%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Anna%20Yojana%20(PMGKAY)%20for%20a%20period%20of%20five%20years%20with%20effect%20from%201st%20January%2C%202024%E2%80%A6%20This%20is%20a%20historic%20decision%20that%20places%20PMGKAY%20amongst%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20social%20welfare%20schemes%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20food%20and%20nutrition%20security%20for%2081.35%20crore%20persons%2C%20at%20an%20estimated%20cost%20of%20Rs.%2011.80%20lakh%20crore%20over%20a%205-year%20period%E2%80%A6%20The%20decision%20reflects%20the%20strong%20commitment%20of%20Hon.%20PM%20Shri%20Narendra%20Modi%20towards%20efficient%20and%20targeted%20welfare%20through%20fulfilment%20of%20basic%20food%20and%20nutrition%20requirements%20of%20the%20population.%20Ensuring%20food%20security%20at%20this%20scale%20during%20Amrit%20Kaal%20would%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20dedicating%20efforts%20towards%20building%20an%20aspirational%20and%20developed%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20suo%20motto%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Fchhattisgarh-assembly%2Fpm-modi-attacks-chhattisgarh-cm-cong-over-betting-app-row-says-they-didnt-even-spare-name-of-mahadev%2Farticle67497413.ece%5C%22%3Eproclaimed%20this%20largesse%20at%20an%20election%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%204%20this%20year.%20%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20I%20want%20to%20tell%20the%20poor%20brothers%20and%20sisters%20of%20the%20country%20from%20the%20land%20of%20Durg%20(Chhattisgarh)%20that%20I%20have%20decided%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20will%20now%20extend%20the%20PMGKAY%20providing%20free%20ration%20to%2080%20crore%20poor%20people%20of%20the%20country%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years.%E2%80%9D%20He%20claimed%20that%20he%20himself%20came%20from%20a%20poor%20family%20and%20he%20considers%20poor%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbiggest%20caste%20%5Bgroup%5D%20in%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scheme%20involves%20free%20supply%20of%20five%20kg%20of%20food%20grains%20per%20month%20to%20over%20810%20million%20people%20who%20account%20for%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rural%20and%20half%20of%20the%20urban%20population.%20The%20scheme%20was%20initiated%20by%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%20in%202013%20under%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%20to%20provide%20subsidised%20food-grains%20to%20the%20poor.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20gone%20through%20changes%20since%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20the%20PMGKAY%20in%202020%20as%20a%20free%20ration%20entitlement%20scheme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fmodi-amrit-kaal-hunger-unemployment%5C%22%3EHunger%20and%20Unemployment%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Amrit%20Kaal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fadmission-of-failure-to-reduce-poverty-hunger-2761143%5C%22%3Eextended%20for%20one%20year%20in%20December%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20country%20was%20recovering%20from%20the%20Covid%20pandemic%20and%20has%20been%20kept%20going%20with%20short%20extensions%20since.%20It%20is%20this%20scheme%20which%20is%20now%20being%20extended%20by%20five%20more%20years%20confirming%20the%20fact%20that%20majority%20of%20Indians%20are%20so%20poor%20that%20they%20cannot%20even%20afford%20to%20buy%20food%2C%20which%20is%20a%20basic%20necessity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20deep%20deprivation%20has%20accelerated%20during%20the%20NDA%20regime%20headed%20by%20Modi%20if%20one%20goes%20by%20the%20Gallup%20World%20Poll%20survey%20for%20India%20focusing%20on%20lack%20of%20money%20to%20buy%20food.%20The%20period%20covered%20in%20the%20study%20is%202018%20to%202021.%20About%2040.2%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20survey%20reported%20not%20having%20enough%20money%20for%20food%20in%202018.%20This%20rose%20to%2048%25%20in%202021.%20In%202023%20it%20seemed%20to%20have%20climbed%20up%20further%20compelling%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sarkariallexams.in%2Fworld-news%2Fa-narrative-of-roti-kapada-aur-makaan-under-the-nda%2F-%5C%22%3Eextend%20the%20%E2%80%98free-ration%E2%80%99%20scheme%20to%20over%20half%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20five%20more%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20abject%20poverty%20is%20further%20evidenced%20by%20the%202023%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%20(GHI)%2C%20wherein%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalhungerindex.org%2Findia.html%5C%22%3EIndia%20ranks%20111th%20out%20of%20the%20125%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20a%20score%20of%2028.7%20in%20the%202023%20GHI%2C%20India%20has%20a%20level%20of%20hunger%20that%20is%20serious.%20GHI%20is%20a%20peer-reviewed%20report%2C%20published%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%20by%20Concern%20Worldwide%20and%20Welthungerhilfe.%20The%20GHI%20is%20a%20tool%20designed%20to%20comprehensively%20measure%20and%20track%20hunger%20at%20global%2C%20regional%2C%20and%20national%20levels%2C%20reflecting%20multiple%20dimensions%20of%20hunger%20over%20time.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20aims%20to%20raise%20awareness%20and%20understanding%20of%20the%20struggle%20against%20hunger%2C%20provide%20a%20way%20to%20compare%20levels%20of%20hunger%20between%20countries%20and%20regions%2C%20and%20call%20attention%20to%20those%20areas%20of%20the%20world%20where%20hunger%20levels%20are%20highest%20and%20where%20the%20need%20for%20additional%20efforts%20to%20eliminate%20hunger%20is%20greatest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fformer-rbi-governor-raghuram-rajan-on-indias-economic-future%5C%22%3EFormer%20RBI%20Governor%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20Economic%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20distressing%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20low-income%20levels%20and%20deprivation%20is%20accompanied%20by%20it%20being%20among%20the%20most%20inequitable%20countries%20in%20the%20world%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findias-richest-1-own-more-than-40-of-total-wealth-oxfam%2Farticle66381944.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20richest%201%25%20owning%20more%20than%2040%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20total%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20bottom%20half%20of%20the%20population%20together%20share%20just%203%25.%C2%A0%20Reality%20is%20that%20the%20rich%20are%20getting%20richer%20while%20the%20poor%20are%20getting%20poorer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20canvas%20that%20a%20near%20ten-fold%20increase%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20per-capita%20GDP%20is%20being%20projected%20to%20be%20achieved%20in%20the%20next%2025%20years.%20NITI%20Aayog%20recently%20announced%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20vision%20document%20%E2%80%98Viksit%20Bharat%20%40%202047%E2%80%99%20to%20make%20India%20a%20%2430%20trillion%20economy%20by%202047%20with%20a%20per%20capita%20GDP%20of%20%2417%2C590%20would%20be%20ready%20by%20December%2C%202023.%C2%A0%20America%E2%80%99s%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20would%20be%20readying%20this%20document%20in%20consultation%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fvision-document-to-make-india-a-30-trillion-economy-by-2047-in-final-stages-draft-to-be-ready-by-december-9005032%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cbusiness%20tycoons%20and%20corporate%20honchos%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20Mukesh%20Ambani%20and%20Gautam%20Adani.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENITI%20Aayog%20CEO%20BVR%20Subrahmanyam%20said%20that%20ten%20sectoral%20groups%20of%20secretaries%20from%20various%20ministries%20created%20around%20themes%20including%20infrastructure%2C%20welfare%2C%20commerce%20and%20industry%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20governance%20have%20each%20prepared%20a%20vision%20document%20in%20a%20process%20that%20lasted%20nearly%20two%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20claimed%20that%20the%20Indian%20economy%20is%20currently%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20fifth%20largest%2C%20with%20a%20size%20of%20%243.75%20trillion.%20The%20annual%20per-capita%20income%2C%20as%20per%20the%20government%20data%2C%20stood%20at%20%E2%82%B998%2C374%20in%202022-23%20i.e.%2C%20%241%2C183.%20Atanu%20Chakraborty%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20HDFC%20Bank%20expects%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Findia-to-be-30-trillion-economy-by-2050-with-per-capita-income-of-21-000-hdfc-bank-chief-atanu-chakraborty-11697031442896.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20Indian%20economy%20to%20become%20the%20third%20largest%20in%20the%20next%20four%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20reach%20the%20%2430%20trillion-mark%20by%202050%2C%20with%20the%20per-capita%20income%20soaring%20to%20%2421%2C000%20by%20then.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBusiness%20tycoon%20Gautam%20Adani%20is%20more%20assertive%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adani.com%2Fblogs%2Findia-on-track-to-becoming-a-25-trillion30-trillion-economy-by-2050-says-gautam-adani%5C%22%3Echips%20in%20with%20this%20gem%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9CFollowing%20independence%2C%20it%20took%20us%2058%20years%20to%20get%20to%20our%20first%20trillion%20dollars%20of%20GDP%2C%2012%20years%20to%20get%20to%20the%20next%20trillion%20and%20just%205%20years%20for%20the%20third%20trillion.%20I%20anticipate%20that%20within%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20India%20will%20start%20adding%20a%20trillion%20dollars%20to%20its%20GDP%20every%2018%20months.%20This%20puts%20us%20on%20track%20to%20be%20a%20%2425-%2430%20trillion%20economy%20by%202050%20and%20drive%20India%E2%80%99s%20stock%20market%20capitalisation%20to%20over%20%2440%20trillion.%E2%80%9D%20And%20he%20adds%20to%20good%20measure%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20country%20is%20now%20the%20most%20exciting%20land%20of%20opportunities%E2%80%9D%20Indeed%2C%20he%20knows%20better!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20realise%20this%20dream%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fvision-document-to-make-india-a-30-trillion-economy-by-2047-in-final-stages-draft-to-be-ready-by-december-9005032%2F%5C%22%3ENITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Subrahmanyam%20advocates%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fvision-document-to-make-india-a-30-trillion-economy-by-2047-in-final-stages-draft-to-be-ready-by-december-9005032%2F%5C%22%3Edrastic%20changes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9C..2047%20will%20be%20a%20very%20different%20India.%20It%20will%20be%20highly%20urbanised.%20Where%20we%20live%2C%20the%20way%20we%20move%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20jobs%20we%20do%2C%20what%20we%20eat%E2%80%93things%20are%20going%20to%20change%20massively%20by%20that%20time%E2%80%A6%20The%20government%20needs%20radical%20restructuring%2C%20both%20horizontally%20and%20vertically%2C%20such%20that%20the%20lower%20levels%20of%20government%20be%20entirely%20tasked%20with%20implementation%20so%20that%20senior%20officials%20can%20spend%20more%20time%20ideating.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20pray%2C%20what%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%20model%E2%80%9D%20to%20achieve%20this%20mammoth%20task%3F%20Predatory%20or%20participatory%3F%20In%20December%20of%202020%2C%20Subrahmanyam%E2%80%99s%20illustrious%20predecessor%20Amitabh%20Kant%20laid%20bare%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freclaimtherepublic.in%2F2021%2F11%2F30%2Fprivatisation-an-affront-to-the-indian-constitution%2F%5C%22%3Eoligarchic-cum-monopolistic%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20promoting%20select%20champions%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20For%20the%20first%20time%20in%20India%20a%20government%20has%20thought%20big%20in%20terms%20of%20size%20and%20scale%20and%20said%20we%20want%20to%20produce%20global%20champions.%20Nobody%20had%20the%20political%20will%20and%20the%20courage%20to%20say%20that%20we%20want%20to%20support%20five%20companies%20who%20want%20to%20be%20global%20champions.%E2%80%9D%20As%20the%20Adani%20story%20unfolds%2C%20we%20see%20this%20model%20being%20practiced%20with%20vengeance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20this%20model%20while%20hunger%20and%20extreme%20inequality%20persists%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20%2430%20trillion%20will%20go%20to%20one%20to%20two%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20would%20look%20like%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20drunken%20stunted%20dog%E2%80%9D%20as%20described%20in%20Aseem%20Shrivastava%20and%20Ashish%20Kothari%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EChurning%20the%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CImagine%20a%20puppy%20which%20is%20fed%20a%20special%20kind%20of%20diet%20which%20distorts%20his%20growth%20so%20that%20one%20of%20his%20legs%20grows%20astonishingly%20fast%2C%20while%20the%20other%20three%20get%20stunted%20to%20various%20degrees.%20Now%20imagine%20that%20the%20puppy%20grows%20into%20a%20dog%20of%20sorts%2C%20gets%20drunk%20and%20begin%20to%20spin%20around%20the%20house%20in%20ecstasy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20wonder%20whether%20this%20is%20the%20fate%20of%20%E2%80%98New%20India%E2%80%99%20in%20%E2%80%98Amrit%20Kaal%E2%80%99%20which%20the%20PIB%20note%20is%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fm-g-devasahayam-2%5C%22%3EM.G.%20Devasahayam%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20former%20Army%20and%20IAS%20officer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701514080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F13084433%2FIMG_1352.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-amrit-kaal-hunger-inequity-and-a-30-trillion-economy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20near%20ten-fold%20increase%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20per-capita%20GDP%20is%20being%20projected%20to%20be%20achieved%20in%20the%20next%2025%20years%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20poverty%2C%20hunger%20and%20unemployment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-amrit-kaal-hunger-inequity-and-a-30-trillion-economy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Weeks%20After%20Indian%20Troops%20Asked%20to%20Leave%20Maldives%2C%20Modi%20Holds%20Talks%20with%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F02160923%2FEffect-9.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20On%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20COP%20summit%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20a%20series%20of%20discussions%20with%20world%20leaders%20ranging%20from%20his%20introductory%20meeting%20with%20the%20newly%20elected%20Maldivian%20president%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20to%20the%20first%20high-level%20interaction%20with%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog%20after%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20significant%20interaction%2C%20Modi%20met%20with%20the%20Maldivian%20President%20in%20Dubai%20on%20Friday%2C%20two%20weeks%20after%20Muizzu%20won%20the%20presidential%20election.%20The%20meeting%20also%20took%20place%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20Maldives%20government%20asking%20India%20to%20withdraw%20Indian%20defence%20personnel%20who%20were%20stationed%20to%20operate%20choppers%2C%20a%20day%20after%20Muizzu%20was%20sworn%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20island%20nation%E2%80%99s%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20outcome%20of%20the%20meeting%20was%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20group%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20India%20or%20a%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20level%20committee%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20press%20note%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37325%2FPrime_Ministers_meeting_with_the_President_of_the_Republic_of_the_Maldives%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20two%20leaders%20%E2%80%9Cdiscussed%20ways%20to%20further%20deepen%20their%20partnership%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccore%20group%E2%80%9D%20was%20a%20result%20of%20this%20direction%20of%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldivian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpresidency.gov.mv%2FPress%2FArticle%2F29241%5C%22%3Epress%20communique%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20declared%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20level%20committee%E2%80%9D%20would%20be%20looking%20to%20enhance%20development%20and%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20people-to-people%20contacts%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fpresidencymv%2Fstatus%2F1730636900619481225%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Maldivian%20president%E2%80%99s%20office%20said%20that%20the%20two%20leaders%20%E2%80%9Cdiscussed%20cooperation%20between%20the%20Maldives%20and%20India%20on%20matters%20of%20concern%20and%20sensitivities%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Maldives%20and%20of%20mutual%20benefit%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20two%20countries%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20however%2C%20no%20more%20details%20about%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20group%20or%20its%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20key%20meeting%20was%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20talks%20with%20Israeli%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog.%20While%20Modi%20has%20spoken%20with%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20this%20was%20the%20highest-level%20meeting%20between%20India%20and%20Israel%20since%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20terror%20attack%20on%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20an%20MEA%20readout%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20exchanged%20views%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Congoing%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20Hamas%20conflict%20in%20the%20region%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20expressed%20his%20condolences%20on%20the%20loss%20of%20lives%20in%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attacks%20and%20welcomed%20the%20release%20of%20hostages%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20reportedly%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20for%20continued%20and%20safe%20delivery%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%20for%20the%20affected%20population%E2%80%9D%20and%20recalled%20India%E2%80%99s%20support%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctwo-state%20solution%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201200%20were%20killed%20by%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%20and%20scores%20were%20taken%20hostage%20in%20Gaza.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20counter-strikes%2C%20which%20included%20airstrikes%20and%20ground%20operations%2C%20killed%20over%2014%2C000%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20seven-day%20pause%20in%20infighting%20to%20allow%20the%20return%20of%20hostages%20ended%20on%20Friday%2C%20with%20Israel%20resuming%20its%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza.%20India%20has%20not%20publicly%20urged%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20and%20it%20had%20abstained%20on%20the%20resolution%20in%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly%20which%20had%20called%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20to%20allow%20for%20supply%20of%20essential%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20PM%20also%20had%20meetings%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37326%2FPrime%2BMinisters%2Bmeeting%2Bwith%2Bthe%2BPresident%2Bof%2Bthe%2BFrench%2BRepublic%5C%22%3EFrench%20President%3C%2Fa%3E%20Emmanuel%20Macron%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37319%2FPrime%2BMinisters%2Bmeeting%2Bwith%2Bthe%2BPresident%2Bof%2Bthe%2BSwiss%2BConfederation%5C%22%3ESwiss%20President%3C%2Fa%3E%20Alain%20Berset%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37324%2FPrime%2BMinisters%2Bmeeting%2Bwith%2Bthe%2BPresident%2Bof%2Bthe%2BRepublic%2Bof%2BUzbekistan%5C%22%3EUzbek%20President%3C%2Fa%3E%20Shavkat%20Mirziyoyev%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37322%2FPrime%2BMinisters%2Bmeeting%2Bwith%2Bthe%2BPrime%2BMinister%2Bof%2Bthe%2BKingdom%2Bof%2BSweden%5C%22%3ESwedish%20PM%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ulf%20Kristersson%20as%20well%20his%20host%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37318%2FPrime%2BMinisters%2Bmeeting%2Bwith%2Bthe%2BPresident%2Bof%2Bthe%2BUnited%2BArab%2BEmirates%5C%22%3EUAE%20President%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sheikh%20Mohamed%20bin%20Zayed%20Al%20Nahyan.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3